A truck was set alight and building equipment vandalised during demonstrations at a construction site this week. CAPE TOWN - The City of Cape Town said it would meet with Hout Bay protest leaders once order had been restored to the area. A truck was set alight and building equipment vandalised during demonstrations at a construction site this week.   A truck was torched during a housing protest in Hout Bay on 17 September 2019. Picture: Supplied The protest is believed to be linked to housing issues. Mayor Dan Plato is set to meet with protesters once the situation has calmed down. Councillor Rob Quintas said: “The mayor feels the access to the area needs to be restored and the matter will be investigated by SAPS.”